<br>
50+ Air pets(including 61 Air) cast:<br>
<br>
AirElementalStrike <br>
1:  Stun(3.0 sec/60) <br>
2:  Decrease Hitpoints by 11 (L1) to 75 (L65) <br>
<br>
The /60 means it can stun up to level 60 mobs.  This is a new flag that some stun spells/effects have recently been given.<br>
<br>
Pre 50 Air Pets cast:<br>
<br>
AirElementalAttack <br>
1:  Stun(3.0 sec/50)<br>
<br>
Meaning they can stun up to 50th level mobs.<br>
<br>
Epic Pet casts:<br>
<br>
ElementalMasteryStrike<br>
1:  Stun(3.0 sec/60) <br>
2:  Decrease Hitpoints by 36 (L1) to 100 (L65) <br>
<br>
Meaning the Epic pet can also stun up to level 60 mobs and with more DD damage as well, just with its lower level compared to Ward of Xegony(49 vs 60) it is far less likely to land the spell.<br>
<br>
I have personally seen Epic pet and 61 Airpet both stun(ie see the stun land and mob freezes for 3 seconds) level 60 mobs in PoD, PoN, Ssra Temple, the 60th level ShikNars in the FG hive caves, and more.<br>
<br>
Clerics, Wizards, and Paladins also got many of their high level stuns flagged this way, stunning up to level 65 mobs on some spells.<br>
<br>
When mobs are hitting for 300-500 in tier 1 PoP zones, a 3 second stun can actually mitigate quite a bit of damage.  Malosini seems to help ALOT.<br>
<br>
I have been in a group on second floor of Ssra with 2 of the 'useless' 58 fire pets chain stunning mobs so much that they never take a swing or cast a spell the whole fight until they die.  Nice if your tank is a ranger or rogue or bard.<br>
<br>
Is 58 Firepet situational?  Aye.  Useless?  Not at all.  Just resummon until you get what I like to call the &quot;Stun Gun&quot; pet.<br>
<br>
Those nasty Sunstrike tossing Snakes in Ssra never know what hit em.<br>
<br>
Try it.<br>
<br>
Sage Finraziel<br>
